JGBs end off earlier lows following stocks ' plunge . Key June Japanese government bond ( JGB ) futures ended Monday ' s Tokyo session down , but well off earlier lows as short - covering pressure intensified following an afternoon plunge in Tokyo stocks , traders said . The June closed down 0 . 35 at 125 . 10 after falling as low as 124 . 63 in the morning . Turnover was 60 , 893 contracts . The Nikkei 225 stock average ended down 589 . 34 points , or 3 . 16 percent , at an intraday low of 18 , 043 . 82 following a media report that Finance Minister Hiroshi Mitsuzuka suggested that the consumption tax could be raised again in the future after a scheduled rise on April 1 . 
